		"description": "<p>At 6th level your power grows as your altered physiology adapts to the life you&rsquo;ve led up to this point. You may choose one of the following abilities and are not bound by your flesh and bone selection.</p>\n<p><strong>Wings of the Beast</strong>: You grow a pair of broad, leathery, wings not unlike those of a bat or a dragon. You gain a fly speed of 40ft. In addition, if you possess the @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.fu6smv03quuleegl]{Beastmantle} bonded power you may now make your tail attack as a ranged weapon attack. It has a range of 20/60 and flings poisoned spines. Your tail&rsquo;s damage increases to 1d10 piercing damage plus Constitution modifier poison damage and any creature damaged becomes poisoned for 1 minute.</p>",
